quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  29,31,"And when Our messengers came to <span class=""h"">Abraham<sup foot_note=""80791"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>with the glad tidings, they said, “We are going to destroy the people of this town; indeed, its people have been unjust.”"
  29,32,"He said, “Yet Lot is in it.” They said, “We know better of who is in it; <span class=""h"">we will most surely</span><span class=""h"">deliver<sup foot_note=""80792"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">him</span>and his family, except for his wife; she has become one of those who linger behind.”"
  29,33,"Then, when Our messengers came to Lot, he was troubled and distressed on their account. But they said, “Do not fear nor grieve; we will <span class=""h"">deliver<sup foot_note=""80793"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">you</span>and your family, except for your wife; she has become one of those who linger behind."
  29,34,"Indeed, <span class=""h"">We will send<sup foot_note=""80794"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">down</span>upon the people of this town a torment from heaven on account of having been defiantly disobedient.”"
  29,35,"And We left behind something of it as an evident sign for people who reason."
  29,36,"And to Midian<i class=""s"">(We sent) </i>their brother Shuʻaib. So he said, “O my people, worship Allah and expect the Last Day, and do not go wickedly about the land, corrupting it.”"
  29,37,"But they disbelieved him, so the Tremor overtook them and they became lifeless bodies in their home."
  29,38,"And ʻĀd{1}and Thamûd{2}as well, as it has become evident for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>from their<i class=""s"">(ruined) </i>residences. And Satan adorned their deeds for them, barring them from the way, even though they could see.",footnotes:1:The pagan tribe of Prophet Hûd.|2:The pagan tribe of Prophet Salih.
